<span id="freeTextContainer2902948147033088334">A powerful spiritual experience, coming from an author still alive!!<br/><br/>I was pleasantly surprised to find out that the author took refuge in France, was living in an inner city project housing at the time he got the Nobel Prize. <br/><br/>A deeply enriching story of his journey, which is at the same time entertaining. A powerful combination of depth and lightness. I haven&apos;t come across a chronicle of journey like this for a long time. It fits so well with his Nobel Prize speech, in wisdom and modesty.<br/></span>
